name: Aristote Garreti
description:
--Fig.26--
Aristote Garreti is a creature from Arber, an exoplanet located 1,3 million light years from Earth.
Besides thier voracious appearence, they only eat small bugs and creatures, using its large neck to stretch into the burrows. Aristotes and both fly and run at very high speeds. They eyes have sensors to all the movements of the planet, so they're always syncronized with the movement of its orb.
